 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "PrintPressAdvisor ⊣ Special-Purpose Machinery Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for ISIC 2829 (Manufacture of other
 special-purpose machinery) -- the RESIDUAL n.e.c. special-purpose-
 machinery category (e.g. printing machinery, plastics/rubber-working
 machinery, mining/construction-adjacent specialty machines), distinct
 from siblings 2812 [fluid power equipment]/2815 [ovens, furnaces and
 furnace burners]/2819 [other general-purpose machinery]/2823
 [machinery for metallurgy] -- this build picks ONE concrete
 illustrative product line, documented plainly in the README:
 industrial printing-press manufacturing (offset presses, flexographic
 presses, gravure presses, digital inkjet presses, screen-printing
 presses, die-cutting presses) -- fabrication and assembly/
 commissioning-bench lines producing finished printing-press machinery
 -- not direct fabrication/assembly-line-equipment control authority
 and not machinery-safety certification authority (e.g. EU Machinery
 Directive 2006/42/EC CE conformity marking or ANSI B65.1 printing-
 press-systems safety conformity marking). Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD
 invariants: propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed
 proposal-effect allowlist (no direct fabrication/assembly-line-
 equipment control), permanent equipment-actuate block, permanent
 machinery-safety-certification-authority block (this actor never
 self-issues a CE/ANSI-B65.1 machinery-safety conformity mark),
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute
 against the batch's own logged production quantity, double-schedule
 guard, product-type validation, registration-accuracy plausibility
 validation, and defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern
 flagging (equipment-safety/quality-defect concern) ALWAYS escalates
 to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
